The single specimen of the Redbank Plains form 5 (QM 
F31697
) consists of a broken nodule an.n

showing two parts of an incomplete carapace: the external impression of the scutes and plates of the partial left lateral border and posterior border of the pleural disc and a part of the peripherals (
Figs 8
; 
9D
); the internal cast showing the impression of the ventral part of the plates of the pleural disc, at the anterior border in an oblique line, from left side at the pleural 2 to right side at the pleural 3 to 5 (
Figs 7
; 
8C
). The anterior part of the pleural disc is hidden by the impression of the external part of the partial left half plastron.

